 of a muscle-related condition.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033704,0.052855,0.059921,0.067002,0.069447,0.073567,0.081176,0.085257,0.092285,0.10539,0.12217,0.15722],"unified_progress":[0.028501,0.047684,0.057607,0.067941,0.071981,0.078778,0.084652,0.090086,0.095567,0.10192,0.12227,0.15301]},{"section":15,"text":"The most common cause of low back pain and stiffness in a young adult without significant structural issues on imaging is fibromyalgia.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030997,0.051923,0.062951,0.070933,0.076162,0.081758,0.088797,0.094869,0.10017,0.10827,0.11106,0.12211],"unified_progress":[0.029452,0.050178,0.06239,0.071856,0.078606,0.086385,0.090694,0.097851,0.10182,0.10631,0.10936,0.11509]},{"section":16,"text":"Fibromyalgia is characterized by widespread musculoskeletal pain, fatigue, and stiffness, especially in the mornings or after rest.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029507,0.049416,0.061893,0.071795,0.085323,0.094995,0.10194,0.10911,0.11118,0.10248,0.091734,0.090627],"unified_progress":[0.031718,0.053963,0.07142,0.081991,0.090147,0.10163,0.10263,0.1047,0.10227,0.09904,0.086632,0.073857]},{"section":17,"text":"The paravertebral tenderness fits because the muscles around the spine are often affected.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041162,0.048907,0.063507,0.075834,0.088122,0.09664,0.10243,0.1062,0.1048,0.096775,0.089691,0.085934],"unified_progress":[0.038893,0.056731,0.07377,0.085655,0.092595,0.099329,0.099645,0.10029,0.099509,0.093382,0.084449,0.075753]},{"section":18,"text":"Another possibility could be myofascial pain syndrome, which is related to muscle knots or trigger points, but fibromyalgia is more systemic with widespread symptoms.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025501,0.043373,0.061821,0.074176,0.088133,0.098111,0.10523,0.11262,0.11432,0.10765,0.092959,0.076113],"u