,0.021387]},{"section":3,"text":"The symptoms started mild","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.13973,0.22647,0.15925,0.086414,0.071878,0.073325,0.054511,0.060472,0.040031,0.035144,0.02926,0.023512],"unified_progress":[0.14619,0.15956,0.12365,0.092443,0.081818,0.084284,0.065438,0.080043,0.051922,0.047229,0.038173,0.02925]},{"section":4,"text":"but now he's having more severe stiffness at night and hip pain.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.14257,0.22601,0.16375,0.092969,0.066275,0.070337,0.051542,0.061281,0.039608,0.03414,0.027987,0.023531],"unified_progress":[0.12831,0.1621,0.12213,0.10437,0.080256,0.084636,0.065672,0.078501,0.055605,0.047755,0.040138,0.030518]},{"section":5,"text":"On exam, there's tenderness in the paravertebral muscles and limited flexion in the lumbar spine.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.1049,0.17725,0.14732,0.10516,0.082763,0.083118,0.065916,0.066989,0.05675,0.043112,0.03632,0.030394],"unified_progress":[0.098359,0.12898,0.11357,0.11052,0.095775,0.092854,0.077872,0.078853,0.071891,0.052992,0.043736,0.034588]},{"section":6,"text":"The X-ray is mentioned but I can't see it, so I have to go off the symptoms and exam findings.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.076822,0.11776,0.11764,0.10826,0.097719,0.089268,0.081163,0.076561,0.068133,0.064869,0.053619,0.048191],"unified_progress":[0.089953,0.095506,0.095248,0.1015,0.098479,0.090902,0.088345,0.083909,0.075079,0.075411,0.058765,0.046906]},{"section":7,"text":"Hmm, back pain in a young adult.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.064884,0.10451,0.11309,0.11117,0.10142,0.088886,0.08368,0.077628,0.06966,0.073016,0.058518,0.053541],"unified_progress":[0.081388,0.084874,0.08922,0.098983,0.096042,0.091521,0.090798,0.087317,0.079678,0.082474,0.065761,0.051943]},{"section":8,"text":"Night pain and stiffness... that makes me think of inflammatory causes rather than mechanical.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050447,0.099549,0.11907,0.11832,0.10533,0.089702,0.08368,0.076254,0.069355,0.074401,0.0587,0.05519],"unified_progress":[0.048143,0.079539,0.089583,0.10127,0.099302,0.095806,0.09512,0.090664,0.085626,0.088962,0.07085,0.055132]},{"section":9,"text":"Conditions like ankylosing spondylitis come to mind.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043578,0.087576,0.10558,0.11127,0.10675,0.096327,0.090817,0.082482,0.074413,0.076447,0.062411,0.062344],"unified_progress":[0.041317,0.06747,0.084593,0.095629,0.098256,0.10177,0.09877,0.094604,0.08971,0.088825,0.074931,0.064127]},{"section":10,"text":"Ankylosing spondylitis typically affects younger males, right?","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036114,0.073652,0.088577,0.10034,0.10633,0.10457,0.1024,0.093359,0.083499,0.083516,0.067355,0.060279],"unified_progress":[0.052326,0.062827,0.080269,0.091061,0.097354,0.10573,0.10127,0.099125,0.092488,0.087644,0.071528,0.058381]},{"section":11,"text":"It's a type of spondyloarthritis.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0349,0.071831,0.086385,0.098163,0.10434,0.1042,0.10298,0.094614,0.084936,0.087981,0.068245,0.061423],"unified_progress":[0.039594,0.062725,0.083526,0.094747,0.099113,0.10579,0.10344,0.10035,0.094096,0.08881,0.071298,0.056515]},{"section":12,"text":"The classic presentation includes chronic back pain, especially worsening at night, which might interfere with sleep.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041955,0.081959,0.085948,0.090038,0.095224,0.098438,0.099311,0.096417,0.088255,0.085012,0.074646,0.062797],"unified_progress":[0.073226,0.074384,0.079166,0.084045,0.089616,0.09608,0.09368,0.095735,0.090892,0.087847,0.075723,0.059607]},{"section":13,"text":"The stiffness is worse in the morning or after inactivity, which fits with the \"stiffness at night\" mentioned here.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053869,0.097256,0.092747,0.089314,0.090668,0.094302,0.09299,0.092497,0.084622,0.079513,0.071189,0.061031],"unified_progress":[0.077066,0.088229,0.087063,0.085812,0.088454,0.092835,0.089471,0.092559,0.085989,0.08224,0.072278,0.058004]},{"section":14,"text":"The physical exam shows paravertebral muscle tenderness.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048294,0.095215,0.098808,0.097055,0.093332,0.093957,0.090913,0.086924,0.089982,0.076086,0.06865,0.060786],"unified_progress":[0.050931,0.084805,0.094742,0.1,0.10211,0.099213,0.094672,0.089825,0.091006,0.075374,0.064356,0.052961]},{"section":15,"text":"In ankylosing spondylitis, there can be inflammation of the sacroiliac joints and the entheses, leading to tenderness around the spine.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036211,0.076615,0.089021,0.098284,0.10178,0.10205,0.10117,0.093611,0.090811,0.081068,0.069731,0.059652],"unified_progress":[0.061223,0.070397,0.087935,0.097015,0.10121,0.1078,0.099421,0.093414,0.089297,0.077693,0.0634,0.051193]},{"section":16,"text":"Limited flexion of the lumbar spine suggests reduced mobility, which could be due to spinal inflammation or possible fusion over time.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035082,0.07694,0.087514,0.094592,0.097556,0.10036,0.10034,0.094773,0.094151,0.082579,0.073511,0.062608],"unified_progress":[0.056169,0.072604,0.086227,0.093804,0.099885,0.10038,0.097304,0.0939,0.091796,0.080815,0.069979,0.057141]},{"section":17,"text":"But since he's 22 and the symptoms are several months, maybe it's early stages.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040458,0.079151,0.087393,0.091523,0.094735,0.099028,0.095857,0.094451,0.089475,0.088658,0.076247,0.063024],"unified_progress":[0.082024,0.10254,0.093185,0.090357,0.089802,0.088304,0.086485,0.088531,0.081046,0.078367,0.066692,0.05267]},{"section":18,"text":"Other possibilities?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034744,0.077487,0.099321,0.10451,0.10075,0.092543,0.09112,0.086699,0.08308,0.089219,0.073826,0.066701],"unified_progress":[0.041072,0.077202,0.088066,0.10303,0.10011,0.09531,0.098823,0.09097,0.086166,0.092959,0.072066,0.054228]},{"section":19,"text":"Maybe mechanical low back pain, but the night pain and hip involvement make me think otherwise.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029174,0.067259,0.083336,0.090789,0.094292,0.094678,0.098821,0.098514,0.095534,0.094414,0.085662,0.067528],"unified_progress":[0.037505,0.064776,0.07893,0.087464,0.094925,0.095877,0.099414,0.10135,0.098557,0.10003,0.082724,0.058458]},{"section":20,"text":"Reactive arthritis?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024455,0.059633,0.076819,0.087658,0.096486,0.10001,0.10352,0.10379,0.099477,0.097104,0.086111,0.064935],"unified_progress":[0.046195,0.068087,0.08234,0.09175,0.096369,0.098711,0.10109,0.10014,0.095139,0.092577,0.075447,0.052162]},{"section":21,"text":"But that's usually after an infection and might have other symptoms like urethritis or conjunctivitis.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019502,0.051805,0.068797,0.08133,0.091784,0.098803,0.10759,0.10944,0.10629,0.10406,0.094519,0.066082],"unified_progress":[0.029548,0.058038,0.075344,0.083794,0.095907,0.10003,0.10317,0.10818,0.10512,0.10716,0.083574,0.050124]},{"section":22,"text":"Inflammatory arthritis like rheumatoid arthritis can affect the spine too, but RA typically involves more symmetric small joints first.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020476,0.052528,0.069023,0.082422,0.092364,0.099263,0.10762,0.10856,0.1049,0.10369,0.091907,0.067243],"unified_progress":[0.03184,0.055733,0.073641,0.084702,0.094674,0.1016,0.10377,0.10811,0.10517,0.10655,0.08319,0.051019]},{"section":23,"text":"The X-ray of the lumbar spine\u2014if it shows sacroiliitis, that would be key.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030616,0.072023,0.086248,0.093602,0.094364,0.097386,0.097752,0.093654,0.10271,0.085771,0.077959,0.067919],"unified_progress":[0.038029,0.070817,0.089007,0.099969,0.10584,0.1035,0.1005,0.095206,0.097833,0.079033,0.067283,0.052984]},{"section":24,"text":"Ankylosing spondylitis often starts with sacroiliac joint inflammation.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029591,0.066269,0.080637,0.09287,0.10001,0.10296,0.10403,0.097713,0.094138,0.087566,0.075981,0.068231],"unified_progress":[0.050574,0.064307,0.081951,0.093882,0.098712,0.11256,0.10173,0.096504,0.091556,0.081885,0.068868,0.057472]},{"section":25,"text":"Early X-rays might not show much, but MRI or CT would be better.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029292,0.06814,0.084276,0.093004,0.096749,0.098708,0.10152,0.098044,0.097044,0.088433,0.080165,0.064626],"unified_progress":[0.05288,0.071533,0.086172,0.094743,0.10117,0.098957,0.098131,0.095515,0.091807,0.085681,0.070104,0.053309]},{"section":26,"text":"However, the question mentions the X-ray is present, so maybe there's some evidence of sacroiliac joint changes.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033428,0.072996,0.08652,0.093044,0.094825,0.096783,0.096489,0.093393,0.096381,0.085933,0.078617,0.071592],"unified_progress":[0.042688,0.076782,0.089896,0.098842,0.10165,0.09787,0.097392,0.091556,0.0902,0.080389,0.071182,0.061552]},{"section":27,"text":"Another thought: diffuse idiopathic skeletal hyperostosis (DISH) but that's more common in older adults.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027199,0.061346,0.0767,0.089657,0.099219,0.10311,0.1057,0.10181,0.095469,0.093523,0.080526,0.06574],"unified_progress":[0.035266,0.063767,0.082972,0.093242,0.098924,0.11111,0.1035,0.10108,0.094815,0.090057,0.072426,0.052846]},{"section":28,"text":"Osteoarthritis could cause back pain but not typically the night stiffness.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022717,0.05539,0.070866,0.082699,0.092204,0.098705,0.10623,0.1069,0.10405,0.10095,0.091888,0.067416],"unified_progress":[0.033816,0.057673,0.074368,0.084105,0.094782,0.099921,0.10209,0.1059,0.10351,0.10661,0.083298,0.053923]},{"section":29,"text":"Infection or tumor?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019471,0.052087,0.070043,0.082046,0.092308,0.098428,0.10546,0.10864,0.10717,0.10372,0.093992,0.066633],"unified_progress":[0.033223,0.06235,0.079466,0.09057,0.097299,0.098974,0.10293,0.10429,0.10122,0.10039,0.079688,0.0496]},{"section":30,"text":"Unlikely without other red flags like weight loss, fever, etc.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.017443,0.047855,0.064224,0.075356,0.085545,0.093598,0.10596,0.11198,0.11219,0.1104,0.1042,0.071246],"unified_progress":[0.025189,0.054967,0.071189,0.079502,0.093147,0.095974,0.10193,0.11058,0.1094,0.11505,0.091106,0.051964]},{"section":31,"text":"So putting it all together: young male, insidious onset, night pain, hip pain, limited spinal mobility, tenderness.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02179,0.047589,0.06015,0.069732,0.080455,0.089551,0.096468,0.101,0.10661,0.10926,0.11453,0.10287],"unified_progress":[0.03266,0.050133,0.062407,0.072856,0.083911,0.095408,0.099336,0.10446,0.10779,0.10811,0.10326,0.079662]},{"section":32,"text":"The most likely diagnosis is ankylosing spondylitis.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020342,0.042929,0.053929,0.06232,0.070155,0.076804,0.084836,0.090225,0.099187,0.10554,0.11938,0.17435],"unified_progress":[0.021377,0.034159,0.043952,0.053342,0.059871,0.076341,0.079711,0.095458,0.10622,0.11125,0.14023,0.17808]},{"section":33,"text":"The classic X-ray findings would include sacroiliitis, which is diagnostic if present.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022623,0.053053,0.066718,0.075759,0.081937,0.087804,0.093814,0.095761,0.10171,0.10155,0.10328,0.11599],"unified_progress":[0.031193,0.046179,0.059065,0.070051,0.077284,0.084748,0.088204,0.095442,0.10162,0.10485,0.11415,0.12722]},{"section":34,"text":"Since the case mentions the X-ray is part of the presentation, even without seeing it, the clinical picture points here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03221,0.062084,0.071094,0.076922,0.082256,0.086942,0.09093,0.093853,0.097196,0.097894,0.098447,0.11017],"unified_progress":[0.040326,0.055897,0.062797,0.070107,0.07543,0.080447,0.084841,0.091575,0.096833,0.10239,0.11328,0.12607]}]}}